Comments: A beneficiary identifier. The HICN that appears in this field is the beneficiary’s current HICN, not necessarily the HICN that was used to process the claim.
Identifies the state where the beneficiary receiving services resides.
Identifies the county where the beneficiary receiving services resides.
The beneficiary’s ZIP code as indicated in their Medicare enrollment record.
The month, day, and year of the beneficiary’s birth.

DataDescription: Beneficiary Age from date of birth
Comments: The beneficiary’s current age, as calculated by subtracting the beneficiary’s date of birth from the current date.

Indicates the reason for a beneficiary's entitlement to Medicare benefits as of a particular date, broken down by the following categories: Old Age & Survivors Insurance (OASI), Disabled, and End Stage Renal Disease (ESRD), and by appropriate combinations of these categories:
10=Aged without ESRD
11=Aged with ESRD
20=Disabled without ESRD
21=Disabled with ESRD
31=ESRD only

Identifies the most recent entitlement status of beneficiaries eligible for a program(s) in addition to Medicare (e.g., Medicaid). Find Dual Status Codes here: http://www.resdac.org/cms-data/variables/Dual-Status-Code-occurs-12-times
The month, day, and year of a beneficiary’s death.
The date the beneficiary enrolled in Hospice.
The date the beneficiary is-enrolled in hospice.
The first name of the beneficiary.
The middle name of the beneficiary.
The last name of the beneficiary.
